<p><b>pra-√viś</b></p> <p>⇒ pūrvva-praviṣṭa~, anu-pra-viṣṭa~, √viś</p><p>§ 4.7.4B6. sarvvehi paṭipāṭikāya piṇḍāya praviśitavyaṃ</p><p>§ 4.7.4B6. bhante etaṃ sidhyati. praviśati bhikṣusaṃgho</p><p>§ 4.8.4B6. yadi tāva hemanto bhavati, anukālaṃ praviśitavyaṃ</p><p>§ 4.8.4B6. atha dāni grīṣmakālo bhavati, śītalakasaṃgena anukālyaṃ praviśitavyaṃ</p><p>§ 4.8.4B7. atha dāni varṣārātro kālo bhavati, devāntarā yeva anukālyaṃ praviśitavyaṃ</p><p>§ 4.9.5A1. praviśa&lt;ṃ>tehi jānitavyaṃ: kathaṃ āsanā prajñaptāḥ</p> <p>§ 4.10.5A2. kāṃsabhājanaṃ parivarjantehi dārakadārikāṃ parivarjantehi praviśitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 4.18.5B7. praviśya vṛddhiye varāye bhūrīye (vs)</p> <p>§ 5.7.6B3. tena praviśiyāṇaṃ (Hs. pravisi°) tahiṃ pṛcchitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 5.7.6B5. bhante etaṃ sidhyati, etaṃ pacyati, praviśantu āryamiśrāḥ!</p> <p>§ 5.8.6B6. anukallatarakaṃ praviśitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 6.7.7B5. yāva sarvvehi paṭipāṭikāye pātrāṇi gṛhṇiya praviśitavyaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ</p> <p>§ 6.9.7B6. tato na kṣamati bhaṇḍam vā ... dārakadārikā laṃghayantehi praviśituṃ. atha khalu bhaṇḍaṃ pariharantehi dārakadārikāṃ pariharantehi praviśitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 6.9.7B7. tato nâpi kṣamati praviṣṭehi gatāgatasya upaviśituṃ</p> <p>§ 8.6.9A2. gocaraṃ praviśantasya grāmapraveśanikāni cīvarāṇi upanāmayitavyāni</p> <p>§ 12.16.12A4. atha dāni evaṃ pi alpāvakāśo bhavati, vṛddhehi cchanne praviśitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 18.20.16A7. bhikṣuḥ uśvāsena uppīḍito nivasanaṃ oguhiya varccakuṭiṃ praviśati</p> <p>§ 18.26.16B3. atha khalu sthāpayitvā praveṣṭavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 18.27.16B3. nâpi dāni kṣamati dantakāṣṭhaṃ khādantena varccakuṭīṃ praveṣṭuṃ</p> <p>§ 18.39.17A2. atha dāni bhikṣuḥ praviṣṭo samāno samudācāra{ṃ}kṛto bhavati, ...</p> <p>§ 19.36.18B7. atha dāni bhikṣuḥ gocaraṃ praviṣṭaḥ praśvāsakṛto bhavati, nâpi kṣamati ...</p> <p>§ 22.4.21A1. cakkalī utkṣipitavyā. nâpi dāni sahasā. anekāyo mā tarhi dīrghako praviṣṭo bhaveya tti</p> <p>§ 22.4.21A2. (vihāraṃ ...) praviśiyāṇaṃ cakkalī osārayitavyā, dvāraṃ bandhitavyaṃ</p> <p>§ 22.6.21A3. vihāraṃ gacchiyāṇaṃ, ... dvāra